This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with Active Appearance Models (AAMs) which are widely used in computer vision for modeling deformable objects. The paper also discusses various optimization methods and cost functions used in fitting AAMs, which are common topics in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the Menpo Project, which is a software library for computer vision and multimedia processing, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
